1
00:02:50,040 --> 00:02:51,159
I brought you food.

2
00:02:51,160 --> 00:02:55,159
I'm not scared of you anymore.
You damn ghost! Die!

3
00:02:55,160 --> 00:02:56,799
Uncle! Uncle!

4
00:02:56,800 --> 00:02:59,279
As much as I regret losing this land,

5
00:02:59,280 --> 00:03:01,559
at least you trust Narathon enough

6
00:03:01,560 --> 00:03:03,399
to let him work on the project he loves.

7
00:03:03,400 --> 00:03:06,120
I don't get it, but my son gets it.
That isn't such a bad balance after all.

8
00:03:08,600 --> 00:03:11,399
Motivation? What is it?

9
00:03:11,400 --> 00:03:12,880
Black Coral.

10
00:03:13,560 --> 00:03:15,120
Black Coral?

11
00:03:21,680 --> 00:03:22,800
You heartless woman.

12
00:03:40,320 --> 00:03:42,239
It hurts.

13
00:03:42,240 --> 00:03:45,880
Anyone, help me.

14
00:04:23,280 --> 00:04:26,040
I never intended to cause you pain.

15
00:04:28,240 --> 00:04:30,920
You've already suffered so much as it is.

16
00:04:34,200 --> 00:04:36,120
Please forgive me.

17
00:04:55,400 --> 00:04:56,680
Good morning.

18
00:04:58,360 --> 00:04:59,319
Well,

19
00:04:59,320 --> 00:05:01,719
don't tell me you're planning
to rent my boat

20
00:05:01,720 --> 00:05:04,600
and go diving for coral
this early in the morning.

21
00:05:05,320 --> 00:05:08,360
Yes. I saw that your shop was closed,
so I didn't dare call out.

22
00:05:09,960 --> 00:05:11,160
Yes, my shop's closed today.

23
00:05:12,840 --> 00:05:13,759
But

24
00:05:13,760 --> 00:05:16,440
you look like
you're about to go diving yourself.

25
00:05:18,960 --> 00:05:20,880
I'm taking care of some personal business.

26
00:05:28,640 --> 00:05:29,520
Kaimook?

27
00:05:32,080 --> 00:05:33,480
You're going diving too?

28
00:05:34,520 --> 00:05:37,320
Yes. And you?

29
00:05:38,320 --> 00:05:41,920
Don't tell me
you're heading to Skull Island too.

30
00:05:43,040 --> 00:05:43,960
Hey.

31
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:47,000
You two are going to Skull Island?

32
00:06:00,520 --> 00:06:01,600
What's going on?

33
00:06:07,440 --> 00:06:08,920
DIVING

34
00:06:23,200 --> 00:06:25,480
Hey, why are you grabbing my hand?

35
00:06:27,720 --> 00:06:29,160
I have something to ask you.

36
00:06:31,920 --> 00:06:35,279
Tell me right now.
Why are you going to Skull Island?

37
00:06:35,280 --> 00:06:40,159
Well, it's nothing.
I'm just going diving and taking photos.

38
00:06:40,160 --> 00:06:41,600
That's not true.

39
00:06:43,320 --> 00:06:46,400
You're going because of the Black Coral
I told you about, aren't you?

40
00:06:49,400 --> 00:06:51,680
I already told you it's dangerous.

41
00:06:53,160 --> 00:06:55,200
Last time we went diving,

42
00:06:56,160 --> 00:06:59,280
there were sudden underwater waves
and a really strange current.

43
00:06:59,800 --> 00:07:02,040
You almost got into serious trouble.
Don't you remember?

44
00:07:03,160 --> 00:07:05,960
And that was
while we were still far from the island.

45
00:07:08,280 --> 00:07:11,760
And what if I told you that
that day, I saw the Black Coral?

46
00:07:12,360 --> 00:07:13,560
Would you believe me?

47
00:07:17,720 --> 00:07:18,720
What?

48
00:07:19,240 --> 00:07:22,160
Why does there always
have to be some kind of problem?

49
00:07:24,760 --> 00:07:27,560
Fine. But hurry up.

50
00:07:29,480 --> 00:07:32,680
Wait. Last night I ran into...

51
00:07:35,960 --> 00:07:39,439
Then let's meet at the event, okay?

52
00:07:39,440 --> 00:07:41,080
Okay.

53
00:07:45,240 --> 00:07:46,440
Where did you go last night?

54
00:07:48,680 --> 00:07:50,000
So you were worried about me?

55
00:07:50,560 --> 00:07:52,679
This is you worrying about me?

56
00:07:52,680 --> 00:07:54,800
By the time I got back,
you were already asleep.

57
00:07:55,440 --> 00:07:57,239
I'm just surprised.

58
00:07:57,240 --> 00:07:59,800
You once told me
you didn't know anyone here except...

59
00:08:02,640 --> 00:08:04,120
So where did you go?

60
00:08:04,800 --> 00:08:07,280
I went drinking at the hotel bar.

61
00:08:10,560 --> 00:08:13,720
I'm going back to Bangkok.
Are you going back or staying here?

62
00:08:15,680 --> 00:08:18,640
I'll go back too.
I only came here because of you.

63
00:08:21,040 --> 00:08:23,320
Good.
Then let's just head back separately.

64
00:08:31,120 --> 00:08:33,239
Just wait until my plan succeeds.

65
00:08:33,240 --> 00:08:35,679
You'll be the one
chasing after me then, Mr. Phum.

66
00:08:40,880 --> 00:08:44,919
I figured you wouldn't believe me.
That's why I didn't tell you that day.

67
00:08:44,920 --> 00:08:46,240
I do believe you.

68
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:49,600
Because I've seen it too.

69
00:08:53,720 --> 00:08:57,160
But you shouldn't go there alone.
It's dangerous.

70
00:08:58,120 --> 00:09:01,520
I already told you.
I don't like leaving things unresolved.

71
00:09:02,560 --> 00:09:03,800
It's extremely dangerous.

72
00:09:06,280 --> 00:09:08,479
We didn't even make it
to Skull Island last time,

73
00:09:08,480 --> 00:09:10,079
and you already saw how terrifying

74
00:09:10,080 --> 00:09:13,160
those currents were. Are you still going?

75
00:09:15,200 --> 00:09:16,799
Then why can you go?

76
00:09:16,800 --> 00:09:19,960
I'm more experienced
at diving than you are.

77
00:09:20,840 --> 00:09:23,560
And if I know it's dangerous,
I'll stop immediately.

78
00:09:24,080 --> 00:09:26,720
Are you saying I'm reckless?

79
00:09:27,320 --> 00:09:31,240
I think you're just
someone who refuses to give up.

80
00:09:33,200 --> 00:09:34,240
Whatever.

81
00:09:35,280 --> 00:09:38,160
But since both of us
have seen the Black Coral,

82
00:09:39,080 --> 00:09:40,120
if it really exists,

83
00:09:40,720 --> 00:09:44,719
I think we should
work together to protect it

84
00:09:44,720 --> 00:09:47,520
before someone
tries to exploit it for profit.

85
00:09:51,000 --> 00:09:52,080
Alright.

86
00:09:53,200 --> 00:09:54,600
But you have to promise

87
00:09:55,120 --> 00:09:57,000
you'll listen to me.

88
00:09:58,400 --> 00:09:59,480
I promise.

89
00:10:02,600 --> 00:10:05,360
But we'll have to wait
until the weather returns to normal.

90
00:10:06,160 --> 00:10:07,400
Not like today.

91
00:10:23,960 --> 00:10:26,479
Na, you're back.

92
00:10:26,480 --> 00:10:28,920
What did you bring me this time?

93
00:10:31,120 --> 00:10:32,000
Here.

94
00:10:32,560 --> 00:10:33,760
What's this?

95
00:10:35,880 --> 00:10:39,280
I stopped by the house in Bangkok
before coming here, so I brought it along.

96
00:10:58,480 --> 00:11:00,799
It's an acceptance letter from SAVE SEA.

97
00:11:00,800 --> 00:11:02,920
I got the internship, Dad.

98
00:11:04,080 --> 00:11:07,640
That's great, Mook.
So you'll have to go back to Bangkok then?

99
00:11:08,320 --> 00:11:09,280
Yes.

100
00:11:10,080 --> 00:11:13,999
You want to go back with me?
I'm going to Bangkok in the evening.

101
00:11:14,000 --> 00:11:15,919
I'm not staying.

102
00:11:15,920 --> 00:11:19,200
Once I finish loading the cargo,
I'll head straight to Singapore.

103
00:11:19,800 --> 00:11:23,000
Perfect. I'm too lazy to drive anyway.

104
00:11:24,480 --> 00:11:26,720
Then I'll be heading back too.

105
00:11:27,400 --> 00:11:31,600
Oh? Won't you stay to do the fish breeding
project with Mr. Narathon.

106
00:11:33,880 --> 00:11:35,920
Not right now.

107
00:11:43,800 --> 00:11:45,240
Are you done yet?

108
00:11:46,000 --> 00:11:48,480
Only these left? Okay.

109
00:12:17,520 --> 00:12:20,160
Hey, is that Skull Island?

110
00:12:22,800 --> 00:12:26,600
Yes, it's the island.

111
00:12:32,000 --> 00:12:34,279
- Hey!
- Hey!

112
00:12:34,280 --> 00:12:36,679
- Let go!
- Stop!

113
00:12:36,680 --> 00:12:39,279
- Ouch!
- You little bitch.

114
00:12:39,280 --> 00:12:40,759
Trying to run away?

115
00:12:40,760 --> 00:12:41,800
- Huh?!
- No!

116
00:12:42,680 --> 00:12:43,640
Hey.

117
00:12:45,280 --> 00:12:47,959
She was trying to escape.
I'm just teaching her a lesson.

118
00:12:47,960 --> 00:12:49,560
I said stop!

119
00:12:55,080 --> 00:12:56,760
- What are you doing?
- No.

120
00:13:01,240 --> 00:13:04,759
Help me.

121
00:13:04,760 --> 00:13:05,880
- Help!
- Give me your hands!

122
00:13:08,040 --> 00:13:09,640
Please let me go.

123
00:13:17,320 --> 00:13:18,880
So?

124
00:13:19,840 --> 00:13:21,559
Why don't you try jumping
into the water and escaping?

125
00:13:21,560 --> 00:13:26,040
You'll sink straight to the bottom
of the sea. You want to?

126
00:13:27,640 --> 00:13:31,880
Yeah, not a bad idea. Then we wouldn't
have to keep watching her.

127
00:13:33,200 --> 00:13:34,520
That's enough.

128
00:13:38,960 --> 00:13:42,680
Shit, we're screwed.
There's a boat coming.

129
00:13:46,760 --> 00:13:49,199
- Help me!
- Hey!

130
00:13:49,200 --> 00:13:50,839
- I've been kidnapped!
- Hey!

131
00:13:50,840 --> 00:13:53,199
- Help me!
- Shut her up!

132
00:13:53,200 --> 00:13:55,760
What are you going to do?

133
00:14:18,080 --> 00:14:19,480
What was that?

134
00:14:22,560 --> 00:14:24,320
Maybe it was just the wind.

135
00:14:33,080 --> 00:14:35,200
Why can't I touch you?

136
00:14:38,560 --> 00:14:41,160
Where did you take my child?

137
00:14:51,040 --> 00:14:53,959
Is the boat ready?

138
00:14:53,960 --> 00:14:56,800
With skills like mine,
you don't have to worry.

139
00:14:58,560 --> 00:15:03,159
If anyone comes to hire the boat,
tell them we're closed for a few days.

140
00:15:03,160 --> 00:15:05,599
Oh? Then why did you
ask me to prepare the boat?

141
00:15:05,600 --> 00:15:08,559
Don't ask too many questions. Get ready.

142
00:15:08,560 --> 00:15:09,840
We've got a big job to do.

143
00:15:11,160 --> 00:15:13,760
What kind of job? Killing someone?

144
00:15:17,080 --> 00:15:18,760
What do you mean by that?

145
00:15:20,160 --> 00:15:21,000
Well...

146
00:15:21,600 --> 00:15:24,959
I was joking. Don't take it so seriously.

147
00:15:24,960 --> 00:15:25,880
Whoa.

148
00:15:28,880 --> 00:15:29,760
Hey.

149
00:15:30,880 --> 00:15:32,680
Don't run your mouth.

150
00:15:33,360 --> 00:15:35,320
If someone hears that,
they'll think we really did it.

151
00:15:35,960 --> 00:15:37,839
And if they report it to the police,

152
00:15:37,840 --> 00:15:40,240
we'll be in deep trouble. Got it?

153
00:15:41,480 --> 00:15:43,400
Alright.

154
00:15:48,760 --> 00:15:50,480
Alright, let's take these things.

155
00:16:12,400 --> 00:16:14,719
Hello, Dad. Hello, Mom.

156
00:16:14,720 --> 00:16:20,480
Hello, Da. Who are you waiting for?
Na or Mook?

157
00:16:22,200 --> 00:16:23,559
Of course she came to wait for me.

158
00:16:23,560 --> 00:16:25,640
I called and told her I was coming back.

159
00:16:26,680 --> 00:16:29,199
Make yourselves at home.
I'm going to rest.

160
00:16:29,200 --> 00:16:30,959
Sitting in the car made me sore.

161
00:16:30,960 --> 00:16:32,519
- Let's go.
- Okay.

162
00:16:32,520 --> 00:16:34,200
- Make yourself at home.
- Alright.

163
00:16:35,560 --> 00:16:36,840
Wait, Mook.

164
00:16:38,320 --> 00:16:41,880
- I came to see you, not Na.
- Oh?

165
00:16:43,200 --> 00:16:46,879
Well, I just wanted to talk
to Mook about the internship, Na.

166
00:16:46,880 --> 00:16:49,760
You got an acceptance letter
from SAVE SEA too?

167
00:16:50,680 --> 00:16:51,920
Yes.

168
00:16:53,200 --> 00:16:55,799
Na, go pack and get ready for the ship.

169
00:16:55,800 --> 00:16:58,160
Once I'm done talking to Mook,
I'll come see you.

170
00:16:59,120 --> 00:17:02,399
Okay. Then I'll let you girls talk.
I'll go get ready.

171
00:17:02,400 --> 00:17:03,360
Okay.

172
00:17:09,040 --> 00:17:09,920
Come here.

173
00:17:10,440 --> 00:17:14,880
- What is it?
- That ghost came again.

174
00:17:16,839 --> 00:17:19,800
Where? To your condo?

175
00:17:20,520 --> 00:17:21,440
Yeah.

176
00:17:22,280 --> 00:17:23,800
She possessed Na too.

177
00:17:24,400 --> 00:17:26,800
Huh? What did you say?

178
00:17:28,680 --> 00:17:29,760
No.

179
00:17:32,840 --> 00:17:34,440
You are the only one who can help me.

180
00:17:35,080 --> 00:17:36,719
No! Stay away from me.

181
00:17:36,720 --> 00:17:38,160
You heartless woman.

182
00:17:42,880 --> 00:17:45,119
She wanted me to help with something.

183
00:17:45,120 --> 00:17:47,800
When I refused, she tried to hurt me.

184
00:17:48,400 --> 00:17:51,399
Luckily, I had the sacred thread.

185
00:17:51,400 --> 00:17:54,160
She got hurt instead and disappeared.

186
00:17:55,520 --> 00:17:57,120
What did Na say?

187
00:17:59,400 --> 00:18:03,040
- I didn't tell him.
- Huh? Why not?

188
00:18:03,840 --> 00:18:07,119
I'm tired of it. He never believes me.

189
00:18:07,120 --> 00:18:09,360
We've fought about it many times already.

190
00:18:12,800 --> 00:18:18,520
I think the woman's spirit
must be in trouble.

191
00:18:19,400 --> 00:18:21,560
She isn't just haunting you for no reason.

192
00:18:22,400 --> 00:18:25,000
You should help her, Da.

193
00:18:26,280 --> 00:18:28,760
What? You want me to help a ghost?

194
00:18:29,600 --> 00:18:32,360
No way. I'm not doing it.

195
00:18:32,960 --> 00:18:34,879
Then what are you going to do?

196
00:18:34,880 --> 00:18:37,880
If you're scared, come stay over with me.

197
00:18:39,880 --> 00:18:45,240
No need. I don't think
she'll dare come near me again.

198
00:18:46,280 --> 00:18:50,040
But just to be safe,
I think I'll stay with Win for a while.

199
00:18:52,440 --> 00:18:53,480
That's good.

200
00:18:58,200 --> 00:18:59,760
Mook,

201
00:19:00,280 --> 00:19:02,480
are you really not going to
give Win another chance?

202
00:19:03,080 --> 00:19:06,480
No. Let's go inside.

203
00:19:13,400 --> 00:19:14,520
Acting so stubborn.

204
00:19:24,360 --> 00:19:29,240
Welcome. I'm truly glad
you both came to intern here.

205
00:19:30,760 --> 00:19:34,319
I'm very happy for the opportunity too.

206
00:19:34,320 --> 00:19:37,639
I promise I'll do my absolute best.

207
00:19:37,640 --> 00:19:40,960
Well, are you both available
to travel upcountry?

208
00:19:41,880 --> 00:19:46,080
Yes, we are.
Will we be traveling with you, Mr. Don?

209
00:19:47,080 --> 00:19:48,279
Not with me.

210
00:19:48,280 --> 00:19:52,720
We have another senior officer
who'll be taking you both to the field.

211
00:19:56,640 --> 00:19:58,760
Come in. Perfect timing.

212
00:20:03,680 --> 00:20:05,200
Mr. Narathon!

213
00:20:06,640 --> 00:20:08,519
Ms. Dara, Ms. Kaimook.

214
00:20:08,520 --> 00:20:10,480
Oh? You know each other?

215
00:20:11,400 --> 00:20:15,519
Yes. We've even gone diving
and had meals together.

216
00:20:15,520 --> 00:20:19,800
That's good. Since you know each other,
working together will be easier.

217
00:20:23,600 --> 00:20:27,439
Does that mean they are
the two students I'll be supervising?

218
00:20:27,440 --> 00:20:30,440
Yes. Ms. Dara and Ms. Kaimook.

219
00:20:38,280 --> 00:20:40,359
GENERAL INFORMATION

220
00:20:40,360 --> 00:20:41,880
Take a look.

221
00:20:42,920 --> 00:20:46,639
This is a rough schedule
for the field trip.

222
00:20:46,640 --> 00:20:49,440
If there's anything
you don't understand, ask me.

223
00:20:53,760 --> 00:20:56,160
We're going to Skull Island?

224
00:20:57,560 --> 00:20:58,440
Yes.

225
00:20:59,240 --> 00:21:01,000
Why does it have to be there?

226
00:21:02,600 --> 00:21:04,840
Because we have a research center there.

227
00:21:06,160 --> 00:21:07,199
Also,

228
00:21:07,200 --> 00:21:09,439
Skull Island's location

229
00:21:09,440 --> 00:21:13,840
is a central point surrounded
by relatively healthy coral reefs.

230
00:21:16,280 --> 00:21:17,160
Oh.

231
00:21:18,120 --> 00:21:18,960
Alright.

232
00:21:20,200 --> 00:21:24,360
If you're not comfortable,
you can tell me.

233
00:21:26,160 --> 00:21:31,000
No, not at all.
The name just sounds scary.

234
00:21:32,400 --> 00:21:36,040
But with you going too,
I'm not scared anymore.

235
00:21:44,520 --> 00:21:48,720
It's lunchtime. Shall we go eat?

236
00:21:50,920 --> 00:21:53,800
Da, we're interns now.

237
00:21:55,760 --> 00:21:59,040
Why? Interns still have to eat.

238
00:22:00,000 --> 00:22:04,000
But Mr. Narathon is our supervisor now.

239
00:22:06,520 --> 00:22:08,160
Oh.

240
00:22:08,720 --> 00:22:11,240
Are we not allowed
to eat with our supervisor?

241
00:22:12,160 --> 00:22:13,720
Of course you are.

242
00:22:14,640 --> 00:22:18,720
Actually, I was going to
invite both of you to lunch anyway.

243
00:22:20,440 --> 00:22:21,560
Shall we go now?

244
00:22:22,920 --> 00:22:25,439
Yes. Let's go.

245
00:22:25,440 --> 00:22:27,040
Let's go, Mook.

246
00:22:33,480 --> 00:22:34,400
Oh, hey.

247
00:22:36,120 --> 00:22:37,600
- Hello, Professor.
- Hello.

248
00:22:38,480 --> 00:22:42,600
So the people you wanted me
to meet are my own students.

249
00:22:45,320 --> 00:22:48,319
Well, Professor Prachaya is also

250
00:22:48,320 --> 00:22:52,160
planning to go collect data there,
so I invited him to come along with us.

251
00:22:55,840 --> 00:22:59,199
Ms. Dara and Ms. Kaimook
are interning with me.

252
00:22:59,200 --> 00:23:02,320
Excellent. Then we need to celebrate.
Here's the menu.

253
00:23:03,080 --> 00:23:04,559
- Order anything you like.
- Thank you.

254
00:23:04,560 --> 00:23:05,680
This meal's on me.

255
00:23:09,480 --> 00:23:11,319
Do you like prawns?

256
00:23:11,320 --> 00:23:14,880
The prawns here are great,
and the seafood sauce is insanely good.

257
00:23:16,000 --> 00:23:18,560
I like eating them.
I just don't like peeling them.

258
00:23:22,760 --> 00:23:25,560
Then I'll peel them for you.
I'm really good at peeling prawns.

259
00:23:26,600 --> 00:23:27,960
Thank you.

260
00:23:29,680 --> 00:23:31,480
Ms. Kaimook,

261
00:23:32,920 --> 00:23:34,320
don't you know how to peel prawns?

262
00:23:36,680 --> 00:23:38,679
Mook can't do things like that.

263
00:23:38,680 --> 00:23:40,520
She only knows how to eat them.

264
00:23:41,840 --> 00:23:42,680
I see.

265
00:23:55,120 --> 00:23:56,640
Two bowls of noodle soup.

266
00:23:57,240 --> 00:23:58,600
And ice too.

267
00:24:06,320 --> 00:24:08,080
- Nice breeze.
- Yeah.

268
00:24:13,680 --> 00:24:16,919
Wait. Why did you bring three glasses?

269
00:24:16,920 --> 00:24:20,840
I saw three of you come in.
Where did the woman go?

270
00:24:23,120 --> 00:24:25,759
What woman? There are only two of us.

271
00:24:25,760 --> 00:24:28,560
But she was just sitting beside you.

272
00:24:30,720 --> 00:24:32,080
Are you crazy?

273
00:24:39,960 --> 00:24:41,160
Don't tell me

274
00:24:42,880 --> 00:24:47,200
you really think a ghost followed us here.

275
00:24:48,520 --> 00:24:49,920
If so, she must be

276
00:24:51,000 --> 00:24:52,520
sitting right beside you now.

277
00:24:57,200 --> 00:25:00,720
Hey, I never knew
you were scared of ghosts too.

278
00:25:09,120 --> 00:25:12,599
- She might be sitting there.
- Just eat. Stop talking so much.

279
00:25:12,600 --> 00:25:14,240
Okay.

280
00:25:35,520 --> 00:25:38,560
Look ahead.

281
00:25:39,240 --> 00:25:42,480
Don't turn around.

282
00:25:48,720 --> 00:25:52,200
It's here! It's here!

283
00:25:54,320 --> 00:25:55,479
It's here!

284
00:25:55,480 --> 00:25:58,439
- It's here.
- What's wrong with him?

285
00:25:58,440 --> 00:26:01,280
You'll die! It's here!

286
00:26:06,640 --> 00:26:09,160
Hey, what's wrong?

287
00:26:10,760 --> 00:26:14,559
You seriously believe
a ghost is following us?

288
00:26:14,560 --> 00:26:17,160
That lunatic's been
spouting nonsense like that forever.

289
00:26:18,640 --> 00:26:22,919
I wasn't thinking a ghost followed us.
It might be a robber.

290
00:26:22,920 --> 00:26:25,120
No harm in staying alert.

291
00:26:25,720 --> 00:26:26,760
Really?

292
00:26:29,360 --> 00:26:32,199
Oh? Hey, wait for me.

293
00:26:32,200 --> 00:26:34,520
Wait for me.

294
00:26:35,480 --> 00:26:37,240
You didn't call me.

295
00:27:14,240 --> 00:27:17,880
I wish for you to move on
to a better realm.

296
00:27:20,960 --> 00:27:22,680
Vengeance

297
00:27:24,160 --> 00:27:26,840
will only keep you in suffering.

298
00:27:46,240 --> 00:27:47,520
Tea, Venerable Sir.

299
00:27:50,560 --> 00:27:51,719
Thank you.

300
00:27:51,720 --> 00:27:53,880
I've been thirsty.

301
00:27:59,120 --> 00:28:00,800
Once you're done, go to bed.

302
00:28:04,000 --> 00:28:04,880
What?

303
00:28:05,840 --> 00:28:06,880
What's the matter?

304
00:28:07,400 --> 00:28:11,640
Well, Venerable Sir,
have you ever seen my father and mother?

305
00:28:14,000 --> 00:28:15,920
Why do you suddenly want to know?

306
00:28:16,760 --> 00:28:19,999
I saw Thon's father. He's a good man,

307
00:28:20,000 --> 00:28:22,239
kind and generous.

308
00:28:22,240 --> 00:28:26,000
So I wanted to know
what my own parents were like.

309
00:28:28,800 --> 00:28:30,840
I never saw your father.

310
00:28:32,040 --> 00:28:33,840
Only your mother.

311
00:28:34,440 --> 00:28:37,160
What was my mother like?
Was she beautiful?

312
00:28:39,520 --> 00:28:44,160
She was beautiful. A good woman.
And she loved you very much.

313
00:28:46,040 --> 00:28:50,320
But she passed away, so I raised you.

314
00:28:53,080 --> 00:28:55,280
How did she die?

315
00:29:00,680 --> 00:29:02,320
It was an accident.

316
00:29:07,880 --> 00:29:08,720
Well.

317
00:29:09,800 --> 00:29:12,120
Go to bed. It's very late.

318
00:29:12,640 --> 00:29:13,640
Yes.

319
00:29:45,000 --> 00:29:48,480
Mom, I miss you.

320
00:29:50,560 --> 00:29:52,840
I want to see you just once.

321
00:29:55,960 --> 00:29:58,040
I want to hug you.

322
00:30:15,840 --> 00:30:18,280
Why did it suddenly get cold?

323
00:30:19,480 --> 00:30:20,880
There's no wind.

324
00:30:27,640 --> 00:30:29,080
My child...

325
00:30:31,280 --> 00:30:33,160
Where are you?

326
00:30:54,080 --> 00:30:58,000
Do you like the photo,
or do you like the person who took it?

327
00:30:58,560 --> 00:30:59,840
Both.

328
00:31:00,800 --> 00:31:01,920
I knew it.

329
00:31:02,640 --> 00:31:05,479
Otherwise, you wouldn't have
bought all these awful photos.

330
00:31:05,480 --> 00:31:07,840
The work isn't even that impressive.

331
00:31:11,320 --> 00:31:13,120
Hello, Mr. Narathon.

332
00:31:15,160 --> 00:31:16,640
Don't be sarcastic with me, Dad.

333
00:31:17,360 --> 00:31:18,479
I'm not being sarcastic.

334
00:31:18,480 --> 00:31:21,760
But if I didn't greet you,
would you even speak to me?

335
00:31:22,400 --> 00:31:26,519
You already know
we have nothing left to talk about.

336
00:31:26,520 --> 00:31:28,640
Not since Mom died.

337
00:32:08,040 --> 00:32:09,600
Give it back.

338
00:32:11,680 --> 00:32:16,120
Ever since I got here,
all I've seen you do is drink.

339
00:32:16,720 --> 00:32:17,560
Hey.

340
00:32:20,520 --> 00:32:24,640
Don't lecture me.
You're my sister, not my mother.

341
00:32:25,400 --> 00:32:27,560
I'm drinking to make the stress go away.

342
00:32:28,440 --> 00:32:29,600
Give it back.

343
00:32:31,560 --> 00:32:35,160
This is exactly why
that rich girl Pat won't look at you.

344
00:32:40,400 --> 00:32:42,880
Da, just shut up.

345
00:32:43,760 --> 00:32:44,640
No.

346
00:32:48,560 --> 00:32:51,279
I warned you not to get involved with her.

347
00:32:51,280 --> 00:32:53,719
She was only using you.

348
00:32:53,720 --> 00:32:57,440
Someone like her would never
look at an ordinary man like you.

349
00:32:58,520 --> 00:33:01,840
Hey, stay out of my business.

350
00:33:04,040 --> 00:33:07,879
If you're going to stay here
and run your mouth,

351
00:33:07,880 --> 00:33:09,960
pack your things
and go back to your condo.

352
00:33:12,680 --> 00:33:14,960
I'm only saying this because I care.

353
00:33:20,640 --> 00:33:23,440
Win, go make up with Mook.

354
00:33:25,040 --> 00:33:29,080
That's impossible.
You know how angry Mook is with me.

355
00:33:29,800 --> 00:33:33,160
That's not true.
She asked about you today.

356
00:33:37,720 --> 00:33:41,519
But now there's someone pursuing her too.
He even studied abroad.

357
00:33:41,520 --> 00:33:44,760
If you're too slow,
you might really lose her for good.

358
00:34:36,679 --> 00:34:38,080
Don't stress so much.

359
00:34:39,400 --> 00:34:43,480
I understand you. You have a son
but it's like you don't.

360
00:34:46,320 --> 00:34:47,920
Then,

361
00:34:49,320 --> 00:34:50,880
why don't we have a child together?

362
00:34:51,840 --> 00:34:55,760
Then you won't have to keep chasing
after your stubborn son anymore.

363
00:35:00,280 --> 00:35:01,720
I do want another child.

364
00:35:05,840 --> 00:35:06,680
Really?

365
00:35:08,360 --> 00:35:09,640
Then...

366
00:35:13,360 --> 00:35:14,640
let's start right now.

367
00:35:18,160 --> 00:35:19,520
But not with you.

368
00:35:21,960 --> 00:35:24,840
You're not fit to be a mother, Sairung.

369
00:35:29,400 --> 00:35:31,200
Then who do you want to have a child with?

370
00:35:32,360 --> 00:35:33,280
Oh.

371
00:35:33,800 --> 00:35:35,200
That little brat Kaimook?

372
00:35:36,240 --> 00:35:40,039
You can't do this to me. I'm your wife.

373
00:35:40,040 --> 00:35:43,079
You need to have a child with me.
I won't allow it.

374
00:35:43,080 --> 00:35:46,399
If you have a child with anyone else,
she'll die.

375
00:35:46,400 --> 00:35:48,280
She'll die!

376
00:35:50,440 --> 00:35:53,400
If you don't stop being
so insanely jealous,

377
00:35:54,160 --> 00:35:55,840
I might lose control one day

378
00:35:56,440 --> 00:35:58,480
and do something you'd never expect.

379
00:36:25,840 --> 00:36:28,440
Why does my stomach hurt now?

380
00:36:40,760 --> 00:36:42,400
- Hey! Snake!
- Don't move.

381
00:37:13,200 --> 00:37:15,120
Can I move now?

382
00:38:01,680 --> 00:38:03,440
Are you worried about Mook?

383
00:38:05,160 --> 00:38:06,639
I thought you were asleep already.

384
00:38:06,640 --> 00:38:08,239
Hm.

385
00:38:08,240 --> 00:38:12,800
How could I sleep
when you keep sighing like that?

386
00:38:18,280 --> 00:38:19,160
Well,

387
00:38:20,160 --> 00:38:21,680
I'm sorry.

388
00:38:22,280 --> 00:38:24,200
I'm really worried about Mook.

389
00:38:25,200 --> 00:38:29,120
She has to stay on that island for days.

390
00:38:30,920 --> 00:38:32,719
But I think what really worries you

391
00:38:32,720 --> 00:38:35,520
is that she has to go with Mr. Narathon.

392
00:38:36,040 --> 00:38:36,960
Right?

393
00:38:39,560 --> 00:38:41,120
That's right too.

394
00:38:42,400 --> 00:38:43,920
But that's only part of it.

395
00:38:45,560 --> 00:38:46,400
Well.

396
00:38:48,880 --> 00:38:50,680
I've got a bad feeling about this.

397
00:38:51,720 --> 00:38:52,640
So,

398
00:38:53,920 --> 00:38:57,159
I heard people have died
on that island before.

399
00:38:57,160 --> 00:38:59,519
Oh, come on.

400
00:38:59,520 --> 00:39:02,120
People die everywhere.

401
00:39:04,960 --> 00:39:07,879
Too bad Na already sailed out.

402
00:39:07,880 --> 00:39:10,320
Otherwise, I'd have asked him
to go with her.

403
00:39:25,000 --> 00:39:26,120
What are you doing?

404
00:39:26,760 --> 00:39:28,319
Lighting herbal scented candles.

405
00:39:28,320 --> 00:39:32,879
The scent helps relieve stress
and makes you sleep better.

406
00:39:32,880 --> 00:39:37,039
I just got these products yesterday,
so it's a good chance to test them.

407
00:39:37,040 --> 00:39:40,079
You're going to light all of those?

408
00:39:40,080 --> 00:39:43,759
Yes. You're so stressed,
so we need a lot of them.

409
00:39:43,760 --> 00:39:46,439
That way, you can relax and sleep.

410
00:39:46,440 --> 00:39:48,559
- Wait, wait.
- What?

411
00:39:48,560 --> 00:39:50,239
If you light them, I'll sleep even less.

412
00:39:50,240 --> 00:39:53,279
I'll be worried the house will catch fire.

413
00:39:53,280 --> 00:39:56,359
Whoa, it won't. You'll sleep well.

414
00:39:56,360 --> 00:40:01,600
Just put them away. I can sleep.

415
00:40:02,200 --> 00:40:03,759
- Can you?
- Yes.

416
00:40:03,760 --> 00:40:05,000
Fine.

417
00:40:06,320 --> 00:40:08,120
- Let's sleep.
- Alright.

418
00:40:10,400 --> 00:40:11,320
Heh.

419
00:40:40,880 --> 00:40:42,440
- Hey! Snake!
- Don't move.

420
00:40:56,480 --> 00:40:57,720
Kang.

421
00:41:01,560 --> 00:41:04,040
Are you sweeping leaves
or just staring at them?

422
00:41:04,920 --> 00:41:06,400
Well...

423
00:41:07,680 --> 00:41:09,040
Uh...

424
00:41:10,200 --> 00:41:11,200
Is something wrong?

425
00:41:11,720 --> 00:41:13,080
Uh...

426
00:41:14,000 --> 00:41:16,639
Last night,
I almost got bitten by a snake.

427
00:41:16,640 --> 00:41:18,840
But a woman saved me.

428
00:41:19,360 --> 00:41:23,280
When I turned around, I didn't see anyone.

429
00:41:26,720 --> 00:41:29,640
So you think it was a ghost.

430
00:41:30,280 --> 00:41:32,720
It wasn't just once, Venerable Sir.

431
00:41:33,640 --> 00:41:35,760
When I almost drowned at the sea,

432
00:41:36,520 --> 00:41:38,640
a woman saved me too.

433
00:41:39,480 --> 00:41:41,400
But after I reached the beach,

434
00:41:42,680 --> 00:41:44,520
I didn't see anyone.

435
00:41:45,720 --> 00:41:48,240
So I was wondering...

436
00:41:49,000 --> 00:41:50,760
Why wonder about it?

437
00:41:51,920 --> 00:41:55,120
You survived twice.

438
00:41:55,720 --> 00:41:58,280
That means your past merit
is protecting you.

439
00:41:58,880 --> 00:42:00,240
So,

440
00:42:01,720 --> 00:42:05,960
as long as you're still alive,
keep doing good deeds.

441
00:42:07,600 --> 00:42:09,120
Remember this, Kang.

442
00:42:09,640 --> 00:42:12,440
Good deeds bring good results.

443
00:42:13,080 --> 00:42:14,600
People who do evil

444
00:42:15,200 --> 00:42:18,760
may escape the law,

445
00:42:20,000 --> 00:42:23,760
but in the end,

446
00:42:24,400 --> 00:42:25,800
no one escapes karma.

447
00:42:29,440 --> 00:42:31,920
Hurry up.

448
00:42:32,440 --> 00:42:34,800
- Yes.
- Go inside when you're done.

449
00:43:19,120 --> 00:43:20,840
No need, Jang.

450
00:43:21,400 --> 00:43:23,640
- Just a cup of coffee is fine.
- Sure.

451
00:43:24,960 --> 00:43:26,760
Thon,

452
00:43:27,400 --> 00:43:30,479
I'm officially opening the gallery
at the end of this week.

453
00:43:30,480 --> 00:43:32,960
I hope you can spare some time to attend.

454
00:43:34,920 --> 00:43:36,200
Don't get your hopes up.

455
00:43:37,360 --> 00:43:41,000
Tomorrow, I'm taking my team
to Skull Island for several days.

456
00:43:42,080 --> 00:43:45,239
I heard the research center there
has been abandoned for years.

457
00:43:45,240 --> 00:43:48,239
Ever since the last group
of researchers all died there.

458
00:43:48,240 --> 00:43:51,199
The news said it was an accident

459
00:43:51,200 --> 00:43:53,520
but people I know said it wasn't.

460
00:43:55,000 --> 00:43:57,640
I didn't know you were
interested in news like that.

461
00:43:58,680 --> 00:44:01,279
I thought you only cared about news

462
00:44:01,280 --> 00:44:03,280
that benefits you.

463
00:44:05,800 --> 00:44:08,320
Can't you stop being sarcastic
with me for once?

464
00:44:10,600 --> 00:44:13,320
I genuinely want to know
why you have to go to Skull Island.

465
00:44:14,160 --> 00:44:15,560
It's my job.

466
00:44:16,880 --> 00:44:18,920
I don't think I need
to report everything to you.

467
00:45:15,960 --> 00:45:18,319
It's here! It's here!

468
00:45:18,320 --> 00:45:21,039
Don't go! Come back!

469
00:45:21,040 --> 00:45:23,239
We're already far from shore.

470
00:45:23,240 --> 00:45:25,000
Can you tell me where we're going now?

471
00:45:25,920 --> 00:45:27,239
To hell.

472
00:45:27,240 --> 00:45:29,439
No. No!

473
00:45:29,440 --> 00:45:32,480
This island is cursed.

474
00:45:40,560 --> 00:45:43,320
Mook, listen to me. I'm sorry.

475
00:45:44,480 --> 00:45:46,119
Can we go back to the way we were?

476
00:45:46,120 --> 00:45:49,679
I have a strange feeling.

477
00:45:49,680 --> 00:45:51,720
I think there's...

478
00:46:25,600 --> 00:46:27,400
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
